MD 10-5 was developed from a cross of MD 15 and JJ 1145ne. MD 15 was developed from a cross of FiberMax 832 and MD 51ne Okra. JJ 1145 is an unreleased breeding line from a cross of JAJO 9596 and JAJO 9550.

The pedigree of PX06520-42-2-1 is: SG747/NM49//AGC85/4364-43. The line derives from an F1XF1 “double cross”. ‘SG747’ derives from a selection out of ‘SG25’, whose parents were ‘SG25’ and DES 119. NM49 is a high fiber quality line from a RIL population created by crossing NM24016 and TM-1. AGC85 is a released breeding line derived from the cultivars ‘FiberMax958 and ‘SG248’. 4364-43 is an unreleased line from an interspecific population derived from the cross of Deltapine 90’ and ‘Pima S-7’.
